The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport
		 Wednesday, August 11, 2004  IN THE CITY
				 																																																	 All the leading cueists of the country including world IBSF snooker champion Pankaj Advani, will take part in the selection trials for the fourth Asian billiards championship and world snooker championship, to be held at the SAI Eastern Centre, here from Friday to Wednesday. This was announced at a press conference on Tuesday.				 																																																	Bangalore will host the Asian meet from October 1 to 8, while the world snooker tourney will be staged in the Netherlands from November 20 to December 4. 				 																																																	 Mohammedan Sporting have issued a memorandum to IFA requesting a cancellation of their CFL Super Division match against Railway FC on Thursday. The club wisheS to play the match on Monday. The club has also asked IFA to discuss Mondays fracas at the Howrah Stadium with the police. 				 																																																	 Mohun Bagan returned to the city from Myanmar on Tuesday evening. Striker Sunil Chhetri, who has malaria, was later admitted to a private city hospital.
